Legs (
Figs. 15-18
). Legs about half length of body. Setal formulae of leg segments as follows (solenidia, in parenthesis): coxae 2 + ( 1 ε p ) - 2 - 2 - 2 ; trochanters 1 - 1 - 2 - 1 ; femora 6 - 5 - 3 - 2 , genua 3 + 1 ĸ - 2 - 0 - 1 ; tibiae 5 + 1 φρ + 1 φ - 5 + 1 φρ - 5 + 1 φρ - 5 + 1 φρ; tarsi 13 + 1 ω - 8 + 1 ω - 7 + 1 ω - 7 + 1 ω. Length of solenidia: I ω 17– 19 , II ω 13–16 , III ω 11–12 , IV ω 8–9 . Coxa I contains supracoxal spine-like seta 1 ε p 3-4 long.

Distribution. This species is recorded from Turkey (
Koç & Ayyilldiz 1997
), Italy (
Berlese 1910
;
Wood 1973
), USA (
Summers 1962
), Germany (
Oudemans 1927
), Ukraine (Kuznetsov 1978 ).
